About the job
We are Quadcode, a company that develops a SaaS trading platform for clients around the world.

Every business is unique, and our banking solution is designed to meet the specific needs of various customer categories. Amaiz is a business account app that is transforming companies and the self-employed across every sector in the UK. Our customers benefit from UK current accounts with customer care, accountancy integration, and smart bookkeeping tools that help them take control of their finances without the hassle.

Now we are looking for Frontend Developer in the Banking Team.

This position can be based in any of the following countries: Armenia, Azerbaijan, Belarus, Bulgaria, Georgia, Greece, Hungary, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Latvia, Moldova, Romania, Serbia.

Tasks in the role


Lead the design, development, and optimization of user-focused, high-performance web applications;
Maintain and enhance web applications using Vue.js;
Collaborate effectively with the UI/UX team to bring innovative user interfaces to fruition;
Prioritize and implement strategies to boost web performance;
Integrate RESTful APIs;
Utilize TypeScript to optimize and enhance the development workflow;
Engage actively in agile development practices and scrum sessions.


Requirements


At least 4 years of frontend development experience using modern JavaScript frameworks, with a focus on Vue.js;
Experience with Quasar framework;
Proficiency in HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript (ES6+);
Experience with cross-browser compatibility and adaptive layouts;
Established expertise in integrating RESTful APIs;
Proficiency in using version control tools, especially Git;
Experience in using Webpack for bundling and optimizing assets;
In-depth knowledge of design patterns, refactoring principles, and code review practices;
Familiarity with agile development methodologies such as Scrum and Kanban;
Practical experience with TypeScript in development projects;
Hands-on experience in creating and executing unit tests to maintain code quality;
Competent written and verbal communication skills (English B1+, Russian B2+);
Proven team player with a structured and goal-oriented approach.


Key Responsibilities:


Lead the design, development, and optimization of user-focused, high-performance web applications;
Maintain and enhance web applications using Vue.js;
Collaborate effectively with the UI/UX team to bring innovative user interfaces to fruition;
Prioritize and implement strategies to boost web performance;
Integrate RESTful APIs;
Utilize TypeScript to optimize and enhance the development workflow;
Engage actively in agile development practices and scrum sessions.


We offer


Remote collaboration from your location;
Competitive remuneration;
Professional courses: from Coursera to Harvard;
Friendly, enjoyable and positive environment.


Ready to be part of a financial revolution? Join us today and be a part of a team that's making banking easier and more efficient for businesses and self-employed individuals. Your journey starts here with Amaiz!

Note: All applications will be treated with strict confidence. We thank all applicants for their interest, however only those candidates selected for interviews will be contacted.
